    <value>3. The name and parameters of variables both support @code</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SitePara.Help4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>4. The content of variable definitions also supports @code and @para, enabling calls between variables and code</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SitePara.Help5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>5. Variable parameters are defined using @para1@ to @para12@ in the content, supporting 12 parameters</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SitePara.Help6" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>6. Condition definitions also support @code and parameters, but do not support variables</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SitePara.Help7" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>7. Condition definitions also support SQL values, defined using @sql:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SitePara.Help8" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>8. Support operation execution. When configuring operation execution, support @code, @para, @sql:, @api_, where @api_ is the interface for data operations and can use the @p@ parameter</value>
